cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper involves machine learning models and natural language processing techniques to identify Russian troll accounts on Twitter, which falls under the sub-categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper discusses the security and privacy implications of these troll accounts, which could also fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and cybercrime (cs.CY).
